Security Consultant Report

After analyzing the college infrastructure, the major cybersecurity risks identified are data breaches, phishing attacks, malware infections, weak passwords and unpatched systems.

The top five recommendations are enabling Multi-Factor Authentication, enforcing strong password policies, regularly updating systems, conducting security awareness training and maintaining regular backups.

These recommendations will improve confidentiality, integrity and availability of important college data. They will reduce cyber threats, prevent unauthorized access and increase overall cybersecurity resilience.

Implementing these measures will help the college maintain a secure digital environment and protect students, faculty and institutional resources from evolving cyber threats.
